      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Under the auspices Of the Struc-\ntural Iron Workers union, the fu-\nneral of Thomas ]. Kelly, who was\nkilled on the Hangman creek grade\nof the Northern Pacific, was held\nthis morning at 10 o'clock from the\nparlors of the Gilman Undertaking\nCo.\n\n\nKelly. age % years, drew No. 81\nin the Occur dAlene Indian land\ndrawing and is believed to have\nbeen on his way here to look over\nthe reservation land when he fell\nbeneath the wheels of train and\nwas killed. He is survived by\nboth parents and by three sisters.\n\n\nMrs. David Binnard, one of the\nsisters, who had written to him\nnotifying him of his success in the\nland drawing, resides in Spokane,\nand the mother of the deceased\nwas making her home with her.\nHis father resides in Butte, Mont,\nwhere the young man was general\nly well known. His other two sis\ntiers are Mrs. Loren, Guardhouse,\nB. c., and Mrs. William Casey,\nPhillipsburg, Canada."
    }
